1. DESCRIPTION OF THE DATASET
SIMSPINE is a research dataset consisting of derived 3D spine keypoint annotations aligned with the Human3.6M dataset.

The dataset contains:
- 15 additional spine-related keypoints generated from Human3.6M sequences
- simulated biomechanical outputs generated using OpenSim
- per-subject OpenSim models (.osim)

The dataset does not contain any original Human3.6M data, including:
- videos
- images
- motion capture recordings
- the original 17 Human3.6M keypoints

The dataset only provides additional annotations that are frame-aligned with Human3.6M sequences.

Use of SIMSPINE therefore requires independent access to the Human3.6M dataset.

2. RELATIONSHIP TO HUMAN3.6M DATASET
SIMSPINE is a derived dataset created using Human3.6M data.

Human3.6M is owned by its respective authors and distributed under its own license agreement.

Users of SIMSPINE must:
- Independently obtain Human3.6M from its official source
- Accept the Human3.6M license agreement
- Use Human3.6M in accordance with its licensing terms

The Human3.6M license can be obtained from: https://vision.imar.ro/human3.6m/

Nothing in this license grants permission to access, distribute, or use Human3.6M data beyond what is permitted by the Human3.6M license.

Users remain fully responsible for complying with the Human3.6M license agreement.

